Three Manchester City key players will miss their Premier League clash against Liverpool on Thursday night at the Etihad Stadium due to injuries and suspension. The players are Sergio Aguero, Fernandinho and Eric Garcia. Liverpool disclosed this in a statement via its official website. “City, meanwhile, will be without Sergio Aguero (knee) and Fernandinho (suspension), while Eric Garcia sustained a head injury in their game versus Arsenal last month and has not featured since,” a club statement on Liverpool’s official website read. Man City lost 2-1 against Chelsea in their last Premier League encounter, while Liverpool defeated Crystal Palace 4-0. The match between Man City and Liverpool will kick-off at 8:15 pm.